      "side": 1,
      "message": "Our thinking here: the original reason for a separate key was schema isolation — to guarantee the regular Exposes schema (exposes_record.json, which carries many fields irrelevant to a platform) is never applied to platform records, only the platform schema.\n\nThat said, the isolation really comes from the Type discriminator rather than the key name (a Type: \"Platform\" config only matches EMPlatformConfig -\u003e platform schema, never EMConfig). So if you still think a single Exposes key is fine, we\u0027re happy to rename it and drop getExposesKey() / the autojson.py change",
      "parentUuid": "a68585f3_d2f00f22",
